INTERESTS & ACTIVITIES
Franco-Belgian Comics (Canon):
Her defining characteristic. Franco-Belgian comics (bandes dessinées) are a huge comic tradition:

The Adventures of Tintin (Hergé) - Belgian
Asterix (Goscinny & Uderzo) - French
Spirou & Fantasio - Belgian
Lucky Luke - Belgian
Gaston Lagaffe - Belgian
The Smurfs - Belgian

These comics are:

Wholesome adventure stories
Ligne claire art style (clear line drawing)
Detailed backgrounds and research
International appeal
Morally upright heroes
Often serialized in magazines first

Why This Matters:

Franco-Belgian comics bridge French and Dutch cultures
Popular in Netherlands, Belgium, France
Represents healthy escapism through adventure and heroism
Creative, artistic interest
Social (these comics are meant to be shared and discussed)

Creative Activities:
Likely draws comics herself (logical inference from her interest):

Always carrying sketchbook
Doodles in notebook margins
Inspired by ligne claire style
Creates adventure stories
Shares work with friends

School Activities:
Possibly in art club or school newspaper (logical for comics lover)
Social and involved in extracurriculars
Part of "nerdy but social" crowd

